s Yoga Routine";s:3:"alt";s:156:"10 minute chair yoga routine for good posture and stress relief once you re done with this routine you ll feel so chair yoga yoga for beginners yoga routine";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/43/53/cf/4353cfbc5347f88f9f3075cbea2078a7.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTuO-PCMOtXqalcSSoEmLFiTgruOKnCrbJD6Q";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:1920;s:6:"height";i:1080;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/113012271888691882/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:71:{i:0;s:54:"A few benefits of chair exercises for seniors include.";i:1;s:195:"Improved flexibility and range of motion Decreased joint pain and stiffness Improved muscle strength and balance Increased blood circulation Elevated mood and concentration Lowered stress levels.";i:2;s:84:"Sit slightly forward in a chair with your feet under you about shoulder-width apart.";i:3;s:92:"Lean slightly forward with the back straight and slowly stand up extending the arms forward.";i:4;s:116:"This exercise is particularly useful for holding objects in front of the body or even just extending an arm forward.";i:5;s:60:"Grab a pair of dumbbells resistance band or a medicine ball.";i:6;s:67:"Sit comfortably in the chair with the hips as far back as possible.";i:7;s:58:"Ensure that the back is firm to the backrest of the chair.";i:8;s:112:"Chair exercises are great for everyone including seniors and anyone looking for ways to stay active as they age.";i:9;s:70:"Learn about some seated and standing chair exercises for seniors here.";i:10;s:50:"The Complete Chair Workout For Seniors Seated Row.";i:11;s:79:"Start in a sturdy chair holding 1-pound hand weights in both hands if you want.";i:12;s:22:"Sit up tall with good.";i:13;s:65:"Designed to work the core muscles the tummy twist should be done.";i:14;s:95:"7 Minute Good Morning Chair Workout for Seniors At Home- Alone or Group No Equipment - YouTube.";i:15;s:49:"20 Wheelchair Seated Exercises for the Elderly 1.";i:16;s:47:"Neck Stretch - Reduces tension around the neck.";i:17;s:57:"Keep your back straight with both feet flat on the floor.";i:18;s:62:"Neck Rotation - Improves flexibility and movement of the neck.";i:19;s:34:"Rotate your neck 360 degrees in a.";i:20;s:48:"Sit upright and away from the back of the chair.";i:21;s:34:"Hold on to the sides of the chair.";i:22;s:64:"Lift your left leg with your knee bent as far as is comfortable.";i:23;s:29:"Place foot down with control.";i:24;s:29:"Repeat with the opposite leg.";i:25;s:28:"Do five lifts with each leg.";i:26;s:101:"Extend your left leg off the floor behind you while reaching out in front of you with your right arm.";i:27;s:92:"Keeping your hips and shoulders squared try to bring that leg and arm parallel to the floor.";i:28;s:42:"Hold then return to the starting position.";i:29;s:53:"Repeat the exercise with your right leg and left arm.";i:30;s:43:"Repeat the exercise on both sides 10 times.";i:31;s:48:"Benefits of Exercise for Seniors in Wheelchairs.";i:32;s:34:"Lowers the likelihood of Diabetes.";i:33;s:48:"Increases muscle strength stamina and endurance.";i:34;s:34:"Improves blood flow and breathing.";i:35;s:38:"Reduces blood pressure in some people.";i:36;s:32:"Improves immune system function.";i:37;s:75:"Lowers chances of getting pressure sores and urinary tract infections UTIs.";i:38;s:33:"The Best Exercises for Seniors 1.";i:39;s:98:"In the past years water aerobics have become an extremely popular form of exercise among all ages.";i:40;s:103:"Like water aerobics chair yoga is a low-impact form of exercise that improves muscle strength mobility.";i:41;s:53:"Stand behind the chair with your feet slightly apart.";i:42;s:39:"Slowly lift your right leg to the side.";i:43;s:73:"Keep your back straight your toe facing forward and stare straight ahead.";i:44;s:28:"Lower your right leg slowly.";i:45;s:45:"Repeat this exercise ten to 15 times per leg.";i:46;s:64:"This balance exercise for seniors can be performed while seated.";i:47;s:45:"9 Floor Games For Your Senior Exercise Class.";i:48;s:65:"Do you have more empty chairs than people in your Exercise Class.";i:49;s:146:"If so then you may want to change a few things this winter like having residents play fun games instead of doing monotonous arm and leg movements.";i:50;s:80:"10 Minute Easy and Effective Chair Exercises for Seniors Chair Yoga for Seniors.";i:51;s:108:"Reduce Pain and Improve Health 3 Easy Tai Chi Videos for Seniors Prevent Falls Improve Balance and Strength.";i:52;s:181:"Chair exercises like stretching are perfect for seniors because they can be adapted for physical limitations minimize the risk of injury due to falls and still give health benefits.";i:53;s:53:"The only equipment needed is a sturdy non-slip chair.";i:54;s:30:"7 Chair Exercises for Elderly.";i:55;s:97:"While sitting sturdily in a chair mimic the motions of a march by lifting the feet off the floor.";i:56;s:139:"Seniors can raise heart rate greater by swinging their arms along with exaggerating and heightening the momentum with each march and swing.";i:57;s:176:"The SmoothRider II exercise cycle is essentially just a pedal exerciser that clips on to the bottom of the chair and provides the option of low-impact cardio and leg exercises.";i:58;s:128:"You might think of this as an exercise of the shoulders and upper back but you can get those abdominal muscles involved as well.";i:59;s:86:"Sit up straight and a bit forward and tighten your abdominal muscles for back support.";i:60;s:68:"Hold your arms out in front of you with your elbows bent 90 degrees.";i:61;s:45:"What if seniors refuse to do chair exercises.";i:62;s:96:"The decision to want to do chair exercises can only be made final by the seniors who will do it.";i:63;s:102:"You cannot force your wishes and also your family or from medical staff to seniors do chair exercises.";i:64;s:92:"Because if forced continuously seniors can 